This paper is about reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on off-policy reinforcement learning algorithms, which are used to learn from data collected by a behavior policy that may be different from the target policy. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Given the focus on machine learning and reinforcement learning, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. However, the paper's emphasis on control and systems analysis suggests that cs.RO and cs.SY are also relevant. Finally, the development of a novel algorithm involves algorithmic design and analysis, which falls under cs.DS.
